       id="database-admin">
   <title>Databases</title>
   <description>Admin REST APIs that operate on databases</description>
   <introduction>
      <paragraph>Admin REST APIs for databases enable administration of Couchbase Server databases (in a few, limited ways) and of the Sync Gateway configuration for the databases. All of the resource URIs contain a path segment for a specific database.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>The following table lists the HTTP methods and URI resource patterns for the Admin REST APIs for databases:</paragraph>
      <table>
         <header>
            <row>
               <entry>HTTP method</entry>
               <entry>URI pattern of the resource</entry>
               <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
         </header>
         <body>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>DELETE</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>GET</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>POST</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/_compact</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>POST</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/_offline</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>POST</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/_online</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>POST</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/_resync</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>PUT</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
            <row>
               <entry>
                  <code>PUT</code>
               </entry>
               <entry>
                  <code>/{db}/_config</code>
               </entry>
               <entry></entry>
            </row>
         </body>
      </table>
      <paragraph>The following table describes the variable path segments of the resource URIs:</paragraph>
         <table>
            <header>
               <row>
                  <entry>Name</entry>
                  <entry>Description</entry>
               </row>
            </header>
            <body>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <code>db</code>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>Name of the database</entry>
               </row>
            </body>
         </table>
   </introduction>
